properties.description: Royce's (1887) map shows a straight line between the point where the boundary line intersects a trail and the point where it meets the Broad River. If such a line was ever surveyed, no trace of it seems to remain.

On Royce's (1887) map, the boundary line appears to generally follow a watershed divide from the head of Shaw Creek to a point where a trail intersects this ridge, near the head of the North Fork of the Edisto River.

According to Royce's (1887) map, this portion of the boundary line follows the Broad River downstream to the confluence with the Saluda River and then downstream along the Congaree River to the mouth of the Wateree River.
